definition: to nibble away at (as silkworm consume leaves)/fig. to embezzle progressively

sentences.english: New office buildings have encroached on the school grounds.
sentences.chinese: 新辦公樓蠶食了學校的操場。

sentences.english: Years could encroach on your beauty , but the abandoned enthusiasm that will make your heart get old.
sentences.chinese: 歲月能蠶食顏容，而放棄熱情卻會老化心靈。

sentences.english: At least one part of the brain, however, now appears to self-cannibalize.
sentences.chinese: 無論如何，至少大腦的一部分現在看來是在自我蠶食。

sentences.english: Months of murderous interest payments gobbled up my savings.
sentences.chinese: 所有積蓄也被幾個月下來的可怕的高額利息蠶食一空。

sentences.english: Inflation has whittled away their savings.
sentences.chinese: 通貨膨脹蠶食了他們的積蓄。

sentences.english: OBJECTIVE To study the feasibility of technique in treatment of Mooren ulcer by transplantation fresh amnion.
sentences.chinese: 目的觀察新鮮羊膜移植治療蠶食性角膜潰瘍的可行性。

sentences.english: Tens of millions of the open-water predators are extracted from global seas every year.
sentences.chinese: 每年，總有數以百萬計的公海生物被人類蠶食。

sentences.english: Nowadays,television white-ants the audiences of the cinema.
sentences.chinese: 近年來，電視蠶食了電影院的觀衆。

sentences.english: It is said that sometimes the victim would be cannibalized.
sentences.chinese: 據說這些受害者有些會被蠶食。

sentences.english: Farming is on the decline in this area as the suburbs gradually encroach.
sentences.chinese: 農業是郊區逐步蠶食，在這方面的下降。
